ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
Health now vs one year ago
Notes: 1 = Much better than a year ago; 2 = Somwehat better; 3 = About the same; 4 = Somewhat worse; 5 = Much worse than a year ago

ElementDescription: Least Desirable State of Health Scale
Health status in general
Notes: 1 = Excellent; 2 = Very good; 3 = Good; 4 = Fair; 5 = Poor

ElementDescription: Health Limitations and Moderate Activity (Daily)
Notes: 1 = Yes, limited a lot; 2 = Yes, limited a little; 3 = No, not limited at all

ElementDescription: Health Limitations and Climbing Stairs (Daily)
Notes: 1 = Yes, limited a lot; 2 = Yes, limited a little; 3 = No, not limited at all

ElementDescription: Physical Health and Accomplishments (Monthly)

Notes: 1 = Not at all ; 2 = A little; 3 = Moderately; 4 = Quite a bit; 5 = Extremely

ElementDescription: Calm and Peaceful (Monthly)
Notes: 1 = All of the time; 2 = Most of the time; 3 = A good bit of the time; 4 = Some of the time; 5 = A little of the time; 6 = None of the time

ElementDescription: Lots of Energy (Monthly)
Notes: 1 = All of the time; 2 = Most of the time; 3 = A good bit of the time; 4 = Some of the time; 5 = A little of the time; 6 = None of the time

ElementDescription: Downhearted and Blue (Monthly)
Notes: 1 = All of the time; 2 = Most of the time; 3 = A good bit of the time; 4 = Some of the time; 5 = A little of the time; 6 = None of the time

ElementDescription: Physical Health or Emotional Problems and Social Activities
Notes: 1 = All of the time; 2 = Most of the time; 3 = Some of the time; 4 = A little of the time; 5 = None of the time
